.TH ucesb 1  "February 26, 2009" "CVS version" "USER COMMANDS"
.SH NAME
ucesb unpacker \- unpack & check every single bit
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B expname/expname
input-specification [OPTIONS]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Read and unpack event-wise experimental data from e.g. nuclear physics
experiments, on a format given by a C structure-like description
(before compilation of the program).
.PP
Provide easy access to the various data members, in form of hbook
ntuple files, root trees, but also in user functions or for quick
viewing from the command line.  Ability to create plots showing the
correlation between data occurring in different detector channels,
often helpful to quickly verify that cabling schemes are correct.  Act
as network server to shoot the event-wise data 'into the back' of any
other program as a simple structure.
.PP
Facilities for acting as a swiss army-knife to manipulate and
transport LMD data over the network.  
