.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Act as a proxy stream server (using the data-content ignoring empty 
program):
.B empty/empty --stream=sourcehost --server=stream
.PP
.SH EXIT STATUS
The unpacker returns 0 if all (requested) events can be retrieved from 
the input sources without excessive unpacking failures (as reported to 
stderr).  Non-0 is returned otherwise.
